{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TZwnnRtgCJz4bD3YRKzMKb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-227.2\"\n3\ttitle: \"Provide PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: high\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\n10\tdepends_on:\n11\t  - \"[[PRD-227.1-core-workflow-template]]\"\n12\tblocks:\n13\t  - \"[[PRD-227.3-migrate-default-workflow]]\"\n14\t  - \"[[PRD-227.4-migrate-extraction-workflow]]\"\n15\timpacts:\n16\t  - src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py\n17\tworkflow: null\n18\ttarget_version: null\n19\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n20\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n21\ttags:\n22\t  - harness\n23\t  - workflow\n24\t---\n25\t\n26\t# Provide PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\n27\t\n28\t## Summary\n29\t\n30\tBundle a built-in `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` that captures the standard PRD implementation lifecycle with PRD-224 invariants enforced. This is the template that most workflows will compose from. It is a declarative definition — the BuiltIns it references either already exist or are introduced by PRD-224.\n31\t\n32\t## Requirements\n33\t\n34\t1. Create `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py` containing `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`.\n35\t2. The template's opening tasks enforce:\n36\t   - `ensure_worktree` (PRD-217 lock + PRD-224.2 stale check)\n37\t   - `set_status(to=\"in-progress\")`\n38\t   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\")`\n39\t3. The template's closing tasks enforce:\n40\t   - `summarize_agent_run` (PRD-224.3)\n41\t   - `commit_transcript` (PRD-224.6)\n42\t   - `set_status(to=\"review\")`\n43\t   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\")`\n44\t   - `push_branch`\n45\t   - `create_pr`\n46\t4. The middle requires at least 1 `AgentTask` and at least 1 `ShellTask`.\n47\t5. The template is importable: `from darkfactory.templates_builtin import PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`.\n48\t\n49\t## Technical Approach\n50\t\n51\t### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n52\t\n53\t```python\n54\tfrom .templates import WorkflowTemplate\n55\tfrom .workflow import BuiltIn, AgentTask, ShellTask\n56\t\n57\tPRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n58\t    name=\"prd-implementation\",\n59\t    description=\"Standard PRD implementation lifecycle with enforced invariants.\",\n60\t    open=[\n61\t        BuiltIn(\"ensure_worktree\"),\n62\t        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"in-progress\"}),\n63\t        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"}),\n64\t    ],\n65\t    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n66\t    middle_required={\n67\t        AgentTask: (1, None),\n68\t        ShellTask: (1, None),\n69\t    },\n70\t    close=[\n71\t        BuiltIn(\"summarize_agent_run\"),\n72\t        BuiltIn(\"commit_transcript\"),\n73\t        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"review\"}),\n74\t        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\"}),\n75\t        BuiltIn(\"push_branch\"),\n76\t        BuiltIn(\"create_pr\"),\n77\t    ],\n78\t)\n79\t```\n80\t\n81\t## Acceptance Criteria\n82\t\n83\t- [ ] AC-1: `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n84\t- [ ] AC-2: The template's `open` list contains `ensure_worktree`, `set_status(in-progress)`, and `commit(start work)` in that order.\n85\t- [ ] AC-3: The template's `close` list contains all PRD-224 invariant tasks (`summarize_agent_run`, `commit_transcript`, `set_status(review)`, `commit(ready for review)`, `push_branch`, `create_pr`) in that order.\n86\t- [ ] AC-4: Composing with no `AgentTask` in the middle raises `TemplateViolation`.\n87\t- [ ] AC-5: Composing with no `ShellTask` in the middle raises `TemplateViolation`.\n88\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7d98639c-26bc-45d3-9705-9d67800b0669","uuid":"48c1014d-1333-423b-87b8-461915476218","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:26:47.132Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-227.2-prd-implementation-template.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-227.2\"\ntitle: \"Provide PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: xs\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.1-core-workflow-template]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.3-migrate-default-workflow]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-227.4-migrate-extraction-workflow]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - workflow\n---\n\n# Provide PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\n\n## Summary\n\nBundle a built-in `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` that captures the standard PRD implementation lifecycle with PRD-224 invariants enforced. This is the template that most workflows will compose from. It is a declarative definition — the BuiltIns it references either already exist or are introduced by PRD-224.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py` containing `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`.\n2. The template's opening tasks enforce:\n   - `ensure_worktree` (PRD-217 lock + PRD-224.2 stale check)\n   - `set_status(to=\"in-progress\")`\n   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\")`\n3. The template's closing tasks enforce:\n   - `summarize_agent_run` (PRD-224.3)\n   - `commit_transcript` (PRD-224.6)\n   - `set_status(to=\"review\")`\n   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\")`\n   - `push_branch`\n   - `create_pr`\n4. The middle requires at least 1 `AgentTask` and at least 1 `ShellTask`.\n5. The template is importable: `from darkfactory.templates_builtin import PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .templates import WorkflowTemplate\nfrom .workflow import BuiltIn, AgentTask, ShellTask\n\nPRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n    name=\"prd-implementation\",\n    description=\"Standard PRD implementation lifecycle with enforced invariants.\",\n    open=[\n        BuiltIn(\"ensure_worktree\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"in-progress\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"}),\n    ],\n    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n    middle_required={\n        AgentTask: (1, None),\n        ShellTask: (1, None),\n    },\n    close=[\n        BuiltIn(\"summarize_agent_run\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit_transcript\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"review\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"push_branch\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"create_pr\"),\n    ],\n)\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n- [ ] AC-2: The template's `open` list contains `ensure_worktree`, `set_status(in-progress)`, and `commit(start work)` in that order.\n- [ ] AC-3: The template's `close` list contains all PRD-224 invariant tasks (`summarize_agent_run`, `commit_transcript`, `set_status(review)`, `commit(ready for review)`, `push_branch`, `create_pr`) in that order.\n- [ ] AC-4: Composing with no `AgentTask` in the middle raises `TemplateViolation`.\n- [ ] AC-5: Composing with no `ShellTask` in the middle raises `TemplateViolation`.\n","numLines":88,"startLine":1,"totalLines":88}}}
